name: Definitions
text:
PART V.  PROVISIONS AFFECTING FINANCIAL STRUCTURE
 
A.  Specific Definitions
 
         For the purposes of sections 302A-1306 to 302A-1309:
     "Enrollment" means the number of students registered in the regular public schools, with each regular student and each special student being counted as one.
     "Moneys" means funds which are not committed to positions. [L 1996, c 89, pt of §2]
 
Note
 
  Sections 302A-1306, 302A-1307, and 302A-1309 referred to in text are repealed.
